Media notes: agitated adult pair giving chips, high chips and high tink calls in alarm, almost certainly as a reaction to my presence (I was probably right near a nest site considering their behavior and me being along the bog edge on Pine Swamp Trail), the closest adult was carrying insects

Locality: Sierra de La Laguna - core area

Observation Details: one at bridge and one near buildings

Background Species: Branta canadensis -- Canada Goose; Sitta carolinensis -- White-breasted Nuthatch

Media notes: also contains a few black and white warbler flight calls and spring peepers

Observation Details: This bird moved from branch to branch in a hardwood forest adjacent to E. Chickamauga Creek.  When perched, it bobbed its hind quarters almost constantly.  It gave both its chip call and its song.

Locality: Shindagin Hollow SF--Shindagin Hollow Rd. Wetland
Media notes: Flight calls from one of a pair of birds; the middle series given in flight, the remainder when the bird was unseen (and thus slightly off focus). The other member of the pair gives a few chip calls in the end of the cut as well.
